Easy date ball recipe! Perfect for when you are craving something sweet 🐰🥕🥕
Recipe 
1 large carrot, peeled
1/4 cup unsweetened shredded coconut
1/4 cup walnuts or nut of choice 
1 cup Medjool dates, pitted (soak in water for 30 minutes) 
1 tsp pure vanilla extract
1 tsp ground cinnamon
1/4 tsp ground ginger
1/4 tsp ground nutmeg
1/4 tsp sea salt
Extra unsweetened shredded coconut for rolling, if desired

It’s Pumpkin Spice Season Witches! 🎃🧙‍♀️

Were celebrating one of the most delicious times of the year with our friends at @slatemilk . We crafted up the most delicious pumpkin spiced latte your lips have ever touched! Best part? It’s keto friendly with 20g or protein and no added sugar! Peep this recipe: 👀

- Half a cup of heavy whipping cream
- 1 teaspoon of pumpkin spice (we used #traderjoes Organic pumpkin Purée)
- 2 tablespoons of pumpkin purée 

Directions:
Pour the half cup of heavy whipping cream into a bowl and whisk till you get whipped cream with stiff peaks

Add the pumpkin purée and spice into the bowl and fold till fully incorporated.

Pour your @slatemilk vanilla latte into a glass with ice.

Add pumpkin whipped cream on top and enjoy!

Let us know what you think of this real easy keto pumpkin spiced latte recipe! #pumpkinspice #ketorecipes #proteinshake #coffeelover

Who wants brownies?! 🎃🍫

These chocolate pumpkin protein brownies are sure to bring a smile to anyone! It’s the perfect snack, a treat to give to your little ones or a dessert after dinner!

We’ve partnered with our friends at @live.momentous to bring you this recipe.

Ingredients:

35 grams @live.momentous Chocolate Whey Protein
100 grams Almond flour
1 tsp Baking soda
75 grams Coconut sugar
1/4 cup Pumpkin purée 
1 Egg

Directions:
Preheat oven to 350 degrees 
While oven is preheating, mix coconut sugar, egg and pumpkin purée in a bowl
Once mixture is incorporated, add dry ingredients
Mix until fully incorporated
Butter 8 inch square brownie pan and add mix into the pan
Bake for 22 minutes
Let cool and cut into 9 separate squares

Enjoy!

Pumpkin season is here! Here’s our top healthier options available at your Trader Joe’s! These are our personal favorites! ♥️🎃

1. Organic Pumpkin- Classic pumpkin purée that makes for a phenomenal pumpkin pie or even for a nice pumpkin whipped cream! 
2. Fall Harvest Salsa- 10/10 salsa. So good! It has pumpkin, tomatoes, water, tomatillos, onions, apple, butternut squash, red bell peppers, jalapeños, honey, lime juice, salt, natural flavors, garlic and cumin. It’s great as a dip or even as a topping to your favorite bowl. 
3. Pumpkin bisque- Great soup to open up and just heat up! It has pumpkin, water, honey, heavy cream, olive oil, tahini, onion, apple cider vinegar, garlic, salt and spices. 
4. Harvest Chili- I’m a chili fan at home so I wasn’t sure I’d like this. It’s really good! It has black beans, onion, tomato, cauliflower, pumpkin, lentils, peppers, garlic, salt, spices 
5. Fall leaf- Ok, these aren’t the cleanest because they have vegetable oils, but they are shaped as leaves. I had to buy because they are so cute! Perfect for hosting a fall event. They have white corn, vegetable oil, yellow corn and spices 

Have you tried any of these Trader Joe’s Fall products? If so, which is your favorite? I’d love to know! 🍂🍁

Have you been including the fantastic five in your diet? Here are the reasons why you should be eating more of these delicious little guys.

Spinach: 🥬
Rich in Nutrients: Spinach is high in vitamins and minerals, particularly iron, which is crucial for oxygen transport in the blood. It's also a good source of vitamins K, A, C, and B2, as well as folic acid, manganese, and magnesium.
Bone Health: The vitamin K content in spinach plays a key role in bone health by helping in the regulation of bone mineralization and maintaining the calcium in bone matrix.

Garlic: 🧄
Heart Health: Garlic is known to have cardiovascular benefits. It can help lower blood pressure and cholesterol levels, reducing the risk of heart disease.
Rich in Antioxidants: Garlic contains antioxidants that can protect against cell damage, potentially reducing the risk of Alzheimer's disease and dementia.

Brussel Sprouts: 🌱
Detoxification Support: Brussel sprouts contain sulfur-containing compounds that are essential for phase II detoxification processes in our body.
Anti-Cancer Properties: Brussels sprouts have compounds called glucosinolates, which have been shown to have anti-cancer properties.

Carrots: 🥕
Eye Health: Carrots are a rich source of beta-carotene, which our bodies convert into vitamin A. This vitamin is essential for good vision, especially in low-light conditions.
Digestive Health: Carrots are a good source of dietary fiber, which promotes healthy digestion and can prevent constipation.

Broccoli: 🥦
Rich in Vitamins and Minerals: Broccoli is packed with a variety of vitamins and minerals, including vitamin C, vitamin K, folate, and potassium.
Anti-Cancer Properties: Broccoli contains a compound called sulforaphane, which has demonstrated potential anti-cancer properties, particularly against certain types of cancers like breast and prostate.
